<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Part of the front of a <rs type="material">white marble</rs> arcaded <rs type="objectType">sarcophagus</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.60</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.71</measure>   × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.11</measure>) cut down for re-use as a Byzantine tomb-cover. Parts of two arcades survive; that on the right enclosed a figure, which has been erased and overcut with a cross.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> within the arcade on the left, of which the right side survives; the text may have continued in further arcades to the right of the figure.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>Second to third centuries A.D. standard forms; <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.018</measure>
</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0101" notAfter="0300" exact="none">Second to third centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>).</p>
</div>
